rComments: If you get used to doing a lot of proofs, this course will be difficult for you. If you haven't done a lot of proofs before, I hope you pass the course
The assignment does not reflect lecture or what we leaned from the course, and the course material are not enough for solving assignment questions.

Confusing lecture
Assignment does not reflect the teaching material
I suppose to graduate this winter sem, but I would rather take this course in the summer. I need to understand the material in this course, but the professor is no help

- In-person lectures are impossible to follow. She goes through the proofs quickly and expects students to understand them in their own time. 

- Examples are rarely given, thus doing her assignment is brutal, even for students who major in Maths like us

- Office hour is not helpful, as she does not allow any questions related to the assignment.

Professor Jemila is great. She is my MAT5375 teacher in my first term of the master's program. Her assignment follows the lecture notes, and she always makes the difficult parts easier to understand. As for the final exam, she gives us one week to finish it, which is really kind for Mathematics students.

I came to the MAT 5375 class after being many years out from my last math course. This course was a challenge given my background but Dr. Hamid was very supportive when I came for assistance. Half way through the course when she received feedback that the course was very difficult she adapted. Her notes were a great adjunctive resource to the text.

Her lectures were ok but she does a lot of theory without proving facts in class and expects students to do proofs in the assignments. It would be nice if she could post solutions to the assignments. She has good notes though, they could be better with more examples and proofs of claims she makes. Her assignments are so time-consuming so beware!
